source: cli/tests/help.rs
expression: text
---
Show or set the per-device scrub throughput limit

Without options, shows the current limit for each device. Use -l with either -a
or -d to set a limit. Pass 0 to -l to remove a limit.

Usage: limit [OPTIONS] <PATH>

Arguments:
  <PATH>
          Path to a mounted btrfs filesystem

Options:
  -a, --all
          Apply the limit to all devices

  -d, --devid <DEVID>
          Select a single device by devid

  -l, --limit <SIZE>
          Set the throughput limit (e.g. 100m, 1g); 0 removes the limit

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
